      • asX509CertificateArray

        public static java.security.cert.X509Certificate[] asX509CertificateArray​(java.lang.Object[] certificates)
                                                                   throws java.lang.ArrayStoreException
        Convert an array into a X509Certificate[].
        Parameters:
        certificates - the certificates (may not be null)
        Returns:
        the X.509 certificate array (not null)
        Throws:
        java.lang.ArrayStoreException - if one of the certificates in the array is not an X509Certificate

      • asOrderedX509CertificateChain

        public static java.security.cert.X509Certificate[] asOrderedX509CertificateChain​(java.security.PublicKey firstPublicKey,
                                                                                 java.security.cert.Certificate[] certificates)
                                                                          throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Convert an unordered array of certificates into an ordered X.509 certificate chain.
        Parameters:
        firstPublicKey - the public key that should be in the first certificate in the ordered X.509 certificate chain (may not be null)
        certificates - the unordered array of certificates (may not be null)
        Returns:
        the ordered X.509 certificate chain, as an array
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given unordered array of certificates cannot be converted into an ordered X.509 certificate chain

      • createX509CertificateChain

        public static java.security.cert.X509Certificate[] createX509CertificateChain​(java.security.cert.X509Certificate firstCertificate,
                                                                              java.util.HashMap<java.security.Principal,​java.util.HashSet<java.security.cert.X509Certificate>> certificatesMap)
                                                                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Create an X.509 certificate chain given the first certificate that should be in the chain and a map of certificates.
        Parameters:
        firstCertificate - the certificate that should be first in the newly created X.509 certificate chain
        certificatesMap - a map of distinguished names to certificates to use to create the X.509 certificate chain
        Returns:
        the newly created X.509 certificate chain, as an array
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the X.509 certificate chain could not be created
